events.name: New York Knicks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons had 30 points and eight assists, and the Portland Trail Blazers erased a 23-point, third-quarter deficit to beat the New York Knicks 112-103 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Simons has 30, Blazers beat Knicks with huge rally in 4th

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 26 points, Desmond Bane added 25 points and four steals, and the Memphis Grizzlies held off the Charlotte Hornets 125-118 on Saturday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies hold off late rally by Hornets to win 5th straight

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 26 points, Domantas Sabonis added 16 points and 11 rebounds in his second game with Sacramento, and the new-look Kings beat the Washington Wizards 123-110 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Sabonis power new-look Kings past Wizards 123-110

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 31 points and 12 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the New Orleans Pelicans 124-114 on Saturday night to give them a pair of double-digit, wire-to-wire road victories in the span of 24 hours.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's 31 points power Spurs past Pelicans, 124-114

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had a triple-double of 40 points, 14 rebounds and 10 assists along with a highlight-reel jam, and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 103-93 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's dunk, triple-double highlight 76ers' win over Cavs

headlines.description: — Rookie guard Bones Hyland made a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 2:16 to play, Nikola Jokic added a pivotal late block, and the Denver Nuggets beat Toronto 110-109 Saturday, ending the Raptors’ winning streak at eight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets beat Raptors 110-109, end Toronto's streak at eight

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo had 19 points and 14 rebounds, and the Miami Heat held off a furious rally from Kyrie Irving and the Brooklyn Nets for a 115-111 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat hold off Irving's charge, hand Nets 11th straight loss

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — It wasn't like the Chicago Bulls asked DeMar DeRozan to deliver yet another dominant performance. Then again, requests aren't needed.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 38, Vucevic dominates as Bulls beat Thunder

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic was unstoppable at the end instead of the beginning in the rematch with the Los Angeles Clippers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Clippers hold off Doncic, Mavs in rematch, 99-97

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 16 of his season-high 33 points in the fourth quarter, Stephen Curry made a clutch layup with 46 seconds remaining, and the Golden State Warriors held off the Los Angeles Lakers 117-115 on Saturday night, spoiling another...
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson has season-high 33, Warriors edge Lakers 117-115

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 26 points and Deandre Ayton had 17 points and 10 rebounds as the Phoenix Suns won their fifth straight game, beating the Orlando Magic 132-105 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker helps NBA-leading Suns past Magic 132-105
